snippet.title: XAmbassadorsVEVO
snippet.description: X Ambassadors – a tight-knit band of brothers and friends who have been playing together for over a decade – broke out with their RIAA-certified gold debut album, VHS (KIDinaKORNER/Interscope) in June 2015. The boundary defying set puts on display vocalist Sam Harris’ propensity for penning anthemic singalongs and the band’s love of music that spans genres and generations. VHS was produced by Grammy Award-winning producer Alex Da Kid and features the platinum selling singles “Renegades” and “Unsteady”.  The band recently released a new song, “Hoping,” to benefit the ACLU. X Ambassadors will co-headline the inaugural Cayuga Sound Festival, along with The Roots, in their home town of Ithaca, NY September 22 – 23. For more information visit www.cayugasoundfestival.com
